                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112/3494</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-23T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 14, 11 a.m. Apparently no obstacle in law of United States to
                    commercial relations between Americans and Germans in China, but as a matter of
                    policy they should be discouraged. How extensive are such relations?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
